 MBOMBELA – Browns has offered a R50 000 reward for any information leading to the successful arrest and prosecution of the suspects who robbed their store in i’langa Mall late on Monday afternoon. Browns security head, Carel Westraad, released screenshots of CCTV footage to the newspaper, saying that it showed people who may be able to help with information about the robbery. A senior members of SAPS’ investigative team authorised Lowvelder to publish these images identifying the suspects to assist them in their investigation. He asked anyone with information to contact him on 083-555-5536.    ALSO READ: Jewellery store robbed at i’langa YOU MAY ALSO BE INTERESTED IN:  Department to smell out speed camera arsonists